-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3615064\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3615064\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 29, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104osu1679559289152.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/osu1679559289152.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/osu1679559289152.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"osu1679559289152\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">net_profile</span> settings defined in the Uniface ASN file helps in\n\t\timproving the security of the LDAP driver on UNIX.</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Arguments</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$LDP = net_profile = &lt;profile_name&gt;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Description</strong></p>\n<div class=\"p\">In the driver settings string on UNIX, you can add the net_profile setting that points to a\n\t\t\tprofile in the NET_SETTINGS. <div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"osu1679559289152__note_ajv_b2d_xwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The settings defined here\n\t\t\t\tapplies strictly for UNIX. For adding settings on Windows, you must refer to the\n\t\t\t\trelevant Microsoft Windows website for details.</div></div>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Example</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">In the following example, a profile in the NET_SETTING is defined and referred from the driver\n\t\t\tsettings: </p>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104osu1679559289152_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"osu1679559289152__codeblock_lvk_3cd_xwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS] \nLDP = U3.0 \nUSYS$LDP_PARAMS nulldefault=N, addbase=off, net_profile=”ldap_settings”</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104osu1679559289152_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"osu1679559289152__codeblock_njp_lcd_xwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[NET_SETTINGS] \nldap_settings= verify_server=yes, verify_server_name=true, ca_certificate=/UNI1040120/ca-bundle.crt, min_tls_version=1.2,cipher_list=HIGH</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"osu1679559289152__note_bsy_bdd_xwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When a profile is defined, and one of the mentioned settings is\n\t\t\tfound in the profile, all network related driver options are ignored. Also, when one of\n\t\t\tthe network options is found in the network profile, the LDAP driver will switch to a\n\t\t\tTLS connection.</div>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Mappings in the settings </strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">The following table provides an overview of the existing driver settings and the network\n\t\t\tprofile settings which replace them when a net_profile is used. When one of the options\n\t\t\tin the second column of the following table is found in the used network profile, the\n\t\t\tLDAP driver will switch to TLS and ignore the settings mentioned in the first column of\n\t\t\tthe table.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"simpletable\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:33.33333333333333%\"/><col style=\"width:33.33333333333333%\"/><col style=\"width:33.33333333333333%\"/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"sthead\">\n<th class=\"stentry\" id=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__1\" scope=\"col\">LDAP driver settings</th>\n<th class=\"stentry\" id=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__2\" scope=\"col\">Net settings</th>\n<th class=\"stentry\" id=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__3\" scope=\"col\">Open LDAP settings and descriptions</th>\n</tr></thead><tbody><tr class=\"strow\">\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tlscadir</span></td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__2\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ca_location</span></td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__3\">Open LDAP setting: <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LDAP_OPT_X_TLS_CACERTDIR</span>\n<p class=\"p\">Directory containing the CA certificates with hashed file names. Sets the\n\t\t\t\t\t\tpath of the directories containing CA certificates.</p></td>\n</tr><tr class=\"strow\">\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tlscafil</span></td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__2\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ca_certificate</span></td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Open LDAP setting: <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LDAP_OPT_X_TLS_CACERTFILESets/</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The full-path of the CA certificate file.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"strow\">\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__2\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Min_tls_version</span></td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LDAP_OPT_X_TLS_PROTOCOL_MIN</span></p>\n<p class=\"p\">1.1 | 1.2 (default)</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Open LDAP does not yet support version 1.3.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"strow\">\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__1\">tls server validation = validate | ignore_name</td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__2\">Verify_server = no (default) | yes</td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Disable server certificate validation when set to “no”.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Maps to the “validate” option when set to “yes”.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"strow\">\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__1\">tls server validation = validate|ignore_name</td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__2\">Verify_server_name = no (default) | yes</td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__3\">Maps to the “ignore_name” option when set to “no”.</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"strow\">\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Cipher_list=&lt;cipherlist&gt;</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"stentry\" headers=\"osu1679559289152__simpletable_spc_tdd_xwb__stentry__3\">Defines the list of ciphers used in the connection, such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ALL </span>,\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">DEFAULT </span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LOW</span>,\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">MEDIUM</span>, or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">HIGH</span><p class=\"p\">The cipher_list can\n\t\t\t\t\t\talso point to a cipher for instance:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">cipher_list=TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA256</span></p></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pqn1665702774521.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>LDAP over TLS</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615064\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615064\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "net_profile (UNIX only) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 29, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The net_profile settings defined in the Uniface ASN file helps in improving the security of the LDAP driver on UNIX. Arguments USYS$LDP = net_profile = <profile_name> Description In the driver settings string on UNIX, you can add the net_profile setting that points to a profile in the NET_SETTINGS. Note: The settings defined here applies strictly for UNIX. For adding settings on Windows, you must refer to the relevant Microsoft Windows website for details. Example In the following example, a profile in the NET_SETTING is defined and referred from the driver settings: Explain this code [DRIVER_SETTINGS] LDP = U3.0 USYS$LDP_PARAMS nulldefault=N, addbase=off, net_profile=”ldap_settings” Copy Explain this code [NET_SETTINGS] ldap_settings= verify_server=yes, verify_server_name=true, ca_certificate=/UNI1040120/ca-bundle.crt, min_tls_version=1.2,cipher_list=HIGH Copy Note: When a profile is defined, and one of the mentioned settings is found in the profile, all network related driver options are ignored. Also, when one of the network options is found in the network profile, the LDAP driver will switch to a TLS connection. Mappings in the settings The following table provides an overview of the existing driver settings and the network profile settings which replace them when a net_profile is used. When one of the options in the second column of the following table is found in the used network profile, the LDAP driver will switch to TLS and ignore the settings mentioned in the first column of the table. LDAP driver settings Net settings Open LDAP settings and descriptions tlscadir ca_location Open LDAP setting: LDAP_OPT_X_TLS_CACERTDIR Directory containing the CA certificates with hashed file names. Sets the path of the directories containing CA certificates. tlscafil ca_certificate Open LDAP setting: LDAP_OPT_X_TLS_CACERTFILESets/ The full-path of the CA certificate file. Min_tls_version LDAP_OPT_X_TLS_PROTOCOL_MIN 1.1 | 1.2 (default) Open LDAP does not yet support version 1.3. tls server validation = validate | ignore_name Verify_server = no (default) | yes Disable server certificate validation when set to “no”. Maps to the “validate” option when set to “yes”. tls server validation = validate|ignore_name Verify_server_name = no (default) | yes Maps to the “ignore_name” option when set to “no”. Cipher_list=<cipherlist> Defines the list of ciphers used in the connection, such as ALL , DEFAULT , LOW , MEDIUM , or HIGH The cipher_list can also point to a cipher for instance: cipher_list=TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA256 Related Links LDAP over TLS Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}